.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-ACCESS 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-access \- access\-management workflows for users, teams, orgs, and service accounts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util access [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run the access\-management command surface for users, orgs, teams, and service accounts.
.IP \(bu 2
List or browse access inventory.
.IP \(bu 2
Create, modify, export, import, diff, or delete access resources.
.IP \(bu 2
Manage service\-account tokens.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B user
List, browse, create, modify, export, import, diff, or delete Grafana users.
.TP
.B org
List, create, modify, export, import, diff, or delete Grafana organizations.
.TP
.B team
List, browse, create, modify, export, import, diff, or delete Grafana teams.
.TP
.B service\-account
List, create, export, import, diff, or delete Grafana service accounts, and manage their tokens.
.TP
.B service\-account token
Add or delete tokens for a Grafana service account.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.IP \(bu 2
\-\-profile, \-\-url, \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
.IP \(bu 2
\-\-prompt\-password, \-\-prompt\-token, \-\-timeout, \-\-verify\-ssl, \-\-insecure, \-\-ca\-cert
.IP \(bu 2
Use the nested subcommands for user, org, team or group, and service\-account.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
grafana-util access user list --profile prod --json
.EE
.EX
grafana-util access service-account list --url http://localhost:3000 --token "$GRAFANA_API_TOKEN" --output-format text
.EE
.EX
grafana-util access service-account token add --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --name deploy-bot --token-name nightly
.EE
.EX
grafana-util access user list --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --scope org --output-format text
.EE
.EX
grafana-util access user add --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --login alice --email alice@example.com --name Alice --password secret
.EE
.EX
grafana-util access user delete --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --login temp-user --scope global --yes --json
.EE
